STUFFED EGGPLANTFor the stuffingOlive oil: 2 tablespoonsOnions: 2 medium, finely choppedGarlic cloves: 3 crushedCarrot: 1 large, finely choppedRed capsicum: 1 large, finely choppedCelery: 2, finely choppedChicken minced: 750gmDiced tomatoes: 400 gmChicken stock: 1 cupTomato paste: 2 tablespoonsBrinjal: 4 largeOlive oilShredded fresh basil leaves: 2/3 cup (keep a few for garnishing)Parmesan cheese: 1 cup gratedMethodHeat oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add onion, garlic, carrot, capsicum and celery. Cook, stirring, for five minutes or until the onion has softened. Add chicken mince. Cook, stirring with a wooden spoon to break up the mince, for five minutes or until browned.Add tomatoes, stock and tomato paste. Bring to boil. Reduce heat to low, cover with a lid and simmer for 30 minutes. Remove cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until thickened.Meanwhile, preheat oven to 180Â°C. Line a baking tray with baking paper. Pierce eggplant several times with a fork. Spray all over with oil. Place on prepared tray. Bake for 40 minutes or until tender. Cool slightly.Cut eggplants in half lengthways. Using a spoon, scoop flesh from the eggplant halves, leaving a one cm border. Fine chop the scooped flesh of brinjal. Combine mince mixture, shredded basil and chopped brinjal in a medium bowl. Place brinjal halves on baking tray. Spoon the prepared mince mixture into brinjal. Sprinkle with parmesan. Bake for 20 minutes or until heated through.Serve sprinkled with basil leaves.WEST COAST FISH CURRYFor the masalaCoconut (fresh andscrapped): half cupOnion (sliced): 1 mediumTomato (chopped):1 mediumCoriander: few springsGarlic: 8 podsGinger: half inchTamarind: small ballCoriander seeds: 2 tbspTurmeric powder: half tspCumin seeds: 1 tspKashmiri dry red chilli: 5Byadgi dry red chilli: 5Pepper cornsGrind the above to a fine paste using one cup of water (if the masala is too thick add more water).For the curryFish: (750 grams of mackerel steaks) wash, drain and apply a little salt and keep aside.Coconut oilOnion (sliced)Green chilli (slit)Tomato (sliced)Water: 2 cupsMethodIn a deep pan heat oil and fry the onion till light brown.Add the masala paste and cook till the raw flavour is gone. Add green chilli,chopped tomato, water and bring to a boil. Once the curry starts to boil add the fish and salt to taste. Cook on a low flame cook for 10 minutes or till the fish is cooked. Serve hot with steamed rice.(The author is chef and culinary manager at Barbeque Nation)